						               													<description>In the humorous and instructive card game Pandemic Poker, everyone wants to protect themselves from the infectious viruses. Mouth and nose protection or disinfectants will benefit you and a few rolls of toilet paper can also help you out.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It is important to keep your distance, also with regard to the playing cards: the cards have different values &amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;and may only be placed on the discard pile with a certain (number) distance. Each card has an additional function that can have an advantage or disadvantage for you or your fellow players. Whoever manages to discard all of his hand cards wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pandemic Poker is Uno with distance rules and strange special abilities. No cards that are directly adjacent to it are placed on the stack, only those values &amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;may be placed that are indicated as permitted on the previous card. After all, we have to keep our distance. In addition, there are special cards that I can play at any time if I have two of the same type. So I suspend or draw cards. Alternatively, I also get rid of CoVid19 cards or swap cards in my hand. And speaking of CoVid19 cards. If we have three of them in hand, we are eliminated from the game. Whoever gets rid of all of his hand cards first wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
